This paper is about neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper compares the performance of different neural network architectures, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of post-edits and error analysis, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as these techniques are also used in image processing.
